review_title: Best Graphics on a roller coaster
one_reviews_text:
I have many roller coaster app... this is the best... Well done... for the graphics and scenery.  I DO NOT AGREE with other reviewers with the ride being slow.  It was a very thoughtful to make it slow so we enjoy the scenery.   THUMBS UP.    

On the flip side,  JUST ANIMATE THE RIVER ... it seemed like ROCK in some areas.

Also ADD MORE VIBRANT  AMBIENT NOISE AND NATURAL SOUNDS , CAVE SOUNDS ETC.     

Overall , great effort and looking forward for more rides.
terrible timing, when you move down it is very slooooowly.

Feel like a wee kitten on the world's tiniest coaster. You'll see pretty much the same statue repeated everywhere on a slow and tiny coaster. Could have been dubbed a train sim as it moves so slowly and there is no mystery to uncover. It is kind of nice and not the worst coaster I've ever ridden, but the ending needs work. It seems scaled very small, and I mean toddler sized. It is charming in it's own way, like an Elder Scrolls fan wanted a Khajiit tumble bug ride and it does that just fine. But now we need fine feline NPCs, yes?
no 3d effect, grotten bad graphic, no cent worth... no stars...
